  "prompt": "How much does an Olympic gold medal cost?",
  "response": "The cost of an Olympic gold medal can be somewhat misleading since Olympic gold medals are not made purely of gold. As of the Tokyo 2020 Olympics, a gold medal is primarily composed of silver, with about 6 grams of pure gold plating. The actual material cost can fluctuate depending on market prices for silver and gold.\n\nAs of 2021, the materials in a gold medal were estimated to be worth around $800 to $1,000 based on current metal prices. However, the true value of a gold medal is often considered to be far greater due to its symbolic significance and the prestige associated with winning an Olympic event. If you were to sell a gold medal, collectors' interest could drive its market value even higher. \n\nIn summary, the material cost of an Olympic gold medal is several hundred dollars, but its true value as a symbol of achievement is much more significant.",
